	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=74761><span id= >Balnore</span></a><br><span id=notbold>99 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.97]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If your main and buddy want to farm some gear for your bard, I'd suggest full Lambent, it's twinking, but if you do all the work (cheap as you only purchase gems) it might work for you.<br><br>As for instruments, I know you don't want to spend a lot of money, but I'd recommend buying the combine instruments from Katta.&nbsp;&nbsp;They are .2 mod better minimum than the regular storebought ones, and drop instruments aren't all that easy to come by.  IF you do want drop ones, Orcish Lute of Singing drops off random orcs from EW to CB I hear, and a free wind instrument would be a scorpian pincer from FoB.<br><br>Then fast weapons are a must as you don't get double attack so the faster the better.  Free would be a Blackened Alloy Long Sword from Splitpaw (just off Misty Thicket). <br><br>Just a few thoughts, there are plenty of options for you.<br><br>Sinfonian</p>&nbsp;<br>Davidon<br>Wood Elf Druid<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547810" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547810</a><br><br>Sinfonian<br>Half-Elf Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835</a></td></td></tr>
