	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Get Ry'Gor armor or Fine Steel Plate.<br><br>Newbie Vah Shir bards dont get armor quests specifically for bards like the other races. However, there are some decent newbie, non-class specific, armor quests in Shar Val and Shadeweaver's Thicket you can do.<br><br>For weapons you can get some fairly decent stuff cheap.&nbsp;&nbsp;Try vendor mining.  I got my primary weapon, Ice Tooth Claws, for 12pp off a vendor. The phosphorecent fiber I use off hand I got from my 48 rogue as a hand me down.<br><br>By farming pelts and spiderling silks as a newbie I was able to get enough together for a guildmate to make me some Fine Steel armor. She did the combines. I either farmed or bought the materials.  I got a full set for about 200pp. The farming was no problem since I was low enough to still get experience for killing the mobs.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
