	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jan 9th 9:23 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>/em nod<br><br>Bards are not tanks.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bards are best played as soloers or in a group support role.  Bards make great pullers.  Bards do decent crowd control. Bards can be short term tanks (like rogues) but should not do this as the main role in a group.<br><br>When soloing the bard can melee fine during the lower levels.  At higher levels a mix of melee and kiting or just straight kiting becomes necessary.<br><br>A lot of folks think that, because bards wear plate armor and carry decent weapons, that we should be main tank or main assist.  Wrong!  We wear plate armor because our songs generate as much aggro as a cleric's healing spells or an enchanter's mezzes and charms.  Its meant to keep us alive and not to make us meatshields.<br><br>We don't do a lot of DPS ourselves.  Our job (one of our jobs anyway) in a group is to help others increase their DPS.<br><br>Bards become heroes by making other folks around them heroes.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
