	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=374><span id=Sage>Sapper</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>26 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.90]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>AGI above 80, below that and you suffer AC wise.<br><br>CHA above 120, is need to help with resists on charm/mez songs<br><br>DEX does help avoid missed notes<br><br>STR adds directly to ATK, helps when you melee<br><br>But the King of stats is HP.&nbsp;&nbsp;STA helps HP, but go for HP, HP, HP whenever possible.   Very few items have just HP, so your other stats will come up a little with them.  We have very few melee songs that DONT give some kind of stat boost as well as haste, so go for HP first.  AC isnt really that big of a deal, although it will reduce the damage you take. <br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Sapper Diesalot, At Deaths Door.&nbsp;&nbsp;"Chuck Berry cant twist this good!"</td></td></tr>
