	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=103963277817950>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103963277817950>RE: Dueling/PvP</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103963277817950#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Dec 11th 2:17 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.47]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Bard PvP strategy changes (just like Bard PvE) with each new level since you gain a new song.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most folks will tell you that dueling a bard is a waste of time unless you catch the bard indoors (where Selo's Accelerando won't work).  Selo's Accelerando with a store bought drum is faster than Spirit of the Wolf. Also, if Selo's is playing at the time a snare or root is cast on the bard the Selo's has a good chance of breaking the snare/root on each pulse.  But, the Selo's has to be playing before the snare/root is cast.  Bard's get very high resist buff songs so it is hard to make a song stick.<br><br>Basically, if you don't catch the bard by suprise winning a PvP encounter is very, very difficult. If the bard starts to lose the bard just runs to the zone.<br><br>Bard's mostly win PvP by attrition, in my experience.  Bard's don't use much mana (only a couple of higher level songs).  Bards have great resists and decent AC.  Bard's can melee or use magic in duels, at their option.  Bard's can regen. Bard's can outrun anyone (except for the most expensive horses).  Bard's can cast while moving.  A bard will just whittle down tough opponents. Make the opponent burn off mana and then whittle away at HP's until the target is dead. <br><br>Most folks I talk to say that bard's are the toughest opponents in PvP.  But winning in PvP as a bard requires patience and a high risk of carpal tunnel syndrome.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
