	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189041><span id=Scholar>Ratguy</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>124 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've just started playing a bard and was looking for some decent newbie armour.&nbsp;&nbsp;Is there any that Vah Shir can use or are we stuck with the Ghulam Armor which is generic to all Vah Shir newbie classes.  It's good for building HP but that's about it.  Since HP isn't the most important stat for Bards I was hoping to get something better, like the true song or wind spirits armour.<br><br>Yeah, I know I could take my ranger out and loot up to twink the bard, but I prefer playing characters from scratch, making them earn thier own way.  I feel I learn more about how to play the character that way.</p>&nbsp;<br>60 season Half Elf Ranger <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=711736" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=711736</a><br><br>38th Season Druid<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=822192" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=822192</a><br><br>Kayne Bayle Server</td></td></tr>
